1
00:00:07,721 --> 00:00:09,481
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

2
00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:41,678
[All characters and events are fictional,
and any resemblance is coincidental]

3
00:00:41,678 --> 00:00:43,075
[Scenes with children and animals were filmed
safely under professional supervision]

4
00:00:44,572 --> 00:00:47,238
This time, I'm asking you.

5
00:00:47,238 --> 00:00:49,738
[Confession is the beginning of forgiveness]
What did you do to that girl?

6
00:00:52,172 --> 00:00:54,005
Do you think I did it?

7
00:00:54,005 --> 00:00:57,438
Obviously, it was the police.

8
00:00:57,438 --> 00:01:00,605
Otherwise, why would they hide the body?

9
00:01:00,605 --> 00:01:04,072
They were all high and mighty
after catching the serial killer,

10
00:01:04,072 --> 00:01:07,505
but they got scared when it looked like
they got the wrong guy, right?

11
00:01:17,705 --> 00:01:19,305
Sir...

12
00:01:23,605 --> 00:01:24,738
Sir.

13
00:01:24,738 --> 00:01:26,172
[Episode 10]

14
00:01:26,172 --> 00:01:28,138
What are you doing here?

15
00:01:30,838 --> 00:01:31,938
I'm asking what you're doing, you punk!

16
00:01:31,938 --> 00:01:34,072
Well, I...

17
00:01:37,172 --> 00:01:40,438
Get it together, you punk. Snap out of it!

18
00:01:40,438 --> 00:01:42,438
I'm asking what you're doing!

19
00:01:45,238 --> 00:01:46,872
Hye Jin is...

20
00:01:48,638 --> 00:01:50,338
dead.

21
00:01:52,805 --> 00:01:54,805
You...

22
00:01:54,805 --> 00:01:56,393
What are you talking about?

23
00:01:56,393 --> 00:01:57,929
I...

24
00:01:57,929 --> 00:02:00,072
I buried...

25
00:02:02,472 --> 00:02:04,238
Hye Jin's body.

26
00:02:11,005 --> 00:02:12,738
Then let's just bury it.

27
00:02:13,505 --> 00:02:15,405
Pardon?

28
00:02:15,405 --> 00:02:16,938
Just for now,

29
00:02:16,938 --> 00:02:19,872
until we catch the real killer.

30
00:02:19,872 --> 00:02:22,372
Still, how could we bury a child...

31
00:02:22,372 --> 00:02:25,038
Did I ever say we're burying a kid alive?

32
00:02:25,038 --> 00:02:28,338
I said just for now.
Do you think I want to do this?

33
00:02:29,438 --> 00:02:30,738
If this gets exposed,

34
00:02:30,738 --> 00:02:32,705
I'll get demoted,
and you'll all be transferred.

35
00:02:32,705 --> 00:02:34,072
We have to step away from this case!

36
00:02:34,072 --> 00:02:36,905
Even if we want to
catch the killer now, we can't!

37
00:02:44,938 --> 00:02:46,569
Your choice.

38
00:02:46,569 --> 00:02:51,705
Cover it up for now and catch
the real killer, or give up altogether.

39
00:02:55,805 --> 00:02:57,438
Park Dae Ho,

40
00:02:59,005 --> 00:03:00,605
go get a shovel.

41
00:03:00,605 --> 00:03:02,405
- Chief!
- Hurry!

42
00:03:03,405 --> 00:03:06,838
Yeah, Dae Ho.

43
00:03:06,838 --> 00:03:10,405
Who will catch the killer if not us?

44
00:03:10,405 --> 00:03:12,272
We'll catch him soon.

45
00:03:17,769 --> 00:03:19,499
Darn it.

46
00:03:24,838 --> 00:03:26,472
But what if

47
00:03:28,672 --> 00:03:30,872
we can't catch him?

48
00:03:39,638 --> 00:03:42,038
That won't happen.

49
00:03:42,038 --> 00:03:43,672
Never.

50
00:04:01,272 --> 00:04:04,905
We'll proceed with Im Seok Man's trial
as planned.

51
00:04:04,905 --> 00:04:06,738
Try him as the serial killer.

52
00:04:06,738 --> 00:04:11,205
Whoever gets caught next
will be labeled the copycat.

53
00:04:11,205 --> 00:04:13,238
Would that be okay, sir?

54
00:04:13,238 --> 00:04:15,272
Why not?

55
00:04:15,272 --> 00:04:17,372
Either way, they'll both
get the death penalty.

56
00:04:18,605 --> 00:04:21,472
I guess that's true.

57
00:04:28,672 --> 00:04:30,472
Is that true?

58
00:04:37,105 --> 00:04:41,338
How could a prosecutor...

59
00:04:41,338 --> 00:04:43,372
How could the police...

60
00:04:43,372 --> 00:04:46,438
How could the police bury a child, you punk!

61
00:04:46,438 --> 00:04:48,605
You should've stopped them no matter what!

62
00:04:48,605 --> 00:04:52,172
You should've done
whatever it took to stop them!

63
00:04:52,172 --> 00:04:54,905
How was I supposed to stop them?

64
00:04:54,905 --> 00:04:57,305
Everyone kept telling me to do it.

65
00:04:58,605 --> 00:05:02,272
How... How was I supposed to refuse?

66
00:05:02,272 --> 00:05:04,105
So you do everything you're told?

67
00:05:04,105 --> 00:05:06,238
What are you, a scarecrow?

68
00:05:06,238 --> 00:05:08,372
You're a human being, you punk!

69
00:05:08,372 --> 00:05:11,072
How could you do something like that?

70
00:05:12,305 --> 00:05:13,772
Sir...

71
00:05:13,772 --> 00:05:16,738
I was scared.

72
00:05:17,938 --> 00:05:21,738
My mother has no one else but me.

73
00:05:22,805 --> 00:05:26,281
I was scared I might not
even make it as a cop.

74
00:05:26,281 --> 00:05:30,538
I was just really scared, sir.

75
00:05:30,538 --> 00:05:33,238
I know I did something wrong.

76
00:05:33,238 --> 00:05:35,538
So I tried to undo it.

77
00:05:35,538 --> 00:05:40,451
I put Hye Jin back where she was
the day before the search.

78
00:05:41,257 --> 00:05:42,605
But...

79
00:05:44,072 --> 00:05:46,638
But!

80
00:05:50,772 --> 00:05:52,538
She was gone...

81
00:05:54,538 --> 00:05:57,138
She vanished without a trace.

82
00:06:05,513 --> 00:06:08,233
Darn it!

83
00:06:08,233 --> 00:06:09,373
Darn it!

84
00:06:16,305 --> 00:06:17,938
Dae Ho.

85
00:06:23,872 --> 00:06:25,938
We need to find Hye Jin.

86
00:06:30,372 --> 00:06:32,938
[Modako]

87
00:06:32,938 --> 00:06:34,538
Si Young!

88
00:06:37,238 --> 00:06:38,805
How long has she been here?

89
00:06:38,805 --> 00:06:40,038
About thirty minutes?

90
00:06:40,038 --> 00:06:42,572
She came straight here looking for you.

91
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:55,972
You're here.

92
00:06:59,338 --> 00:07:02,172
So these are the girls
you've been fooling around with?

93
00:07:03,238 --> 00:07:04,872
Everyone, get out.

94
00:07:13,772 --> 00:07:14,805
What brings you here?

95
00:07:14,805 --> 00:07:17,305
I heard you are a regular here.

96
00:07:17,305 --> 00:07:20,738
So I wanted to see what kind of place it is.

97
00:07:23,005 --> 00:07:25,538
Why didn't you say anything?

98
00:07:25,538 --> 00:07:29,172
Oh, the owner here was a classmate of mine.

99
00:07:29,172 --> 00:07:30,665
No,

100
00:07:30,665 --> 00:07:32,572
not that.

101
00:07:33,805 --> 00:07:36,105
About your mother, Si Young.

102
00:07:38,938 --> 00:07:42,272
How long were you planning to hide the truth?

103
00:07:47,805 --> 00:07:49,472
How did you find out?

104
00:07:50,705 --> 00:07:53,072
Does that really matter?

105
00:07:53,705 --> 00:07:57,372
My father says it doesn't matter
since you're on the family registry.

106
00:07:58,772 --> 00:08:00,195
But not to me.

107
00:08:01,005 --> 00:08:03,338
The bloodline of a bar hostess?

108
00:08:03,338 --> 00:08:05,805
My child could inherit that blood.

109
00:08:05,805 --> 00:08:09,705
It just feels filthy to me.

110
00:08:14,005 --> 00:08:15,905
My blood is filthy?

111
00:08:16,972 --> 00:08:19,305
If that offended you, I apologize.

112
00:08:19,972 --> 00:08:22,005
You'll call off the wedding, right?

113
00:08:25,372 --> 00:08:27,372
I can't let that happen.

114
00:08:30,972 --> 00:08:33,449
Even if I expose your father's
illegitimate child

115
00:08:33,449 --> 00:08:36,072
to the world?

116
00:08:36,072 --> 00:08:38,772
I could destroy your father's

117
00:08:39,672 --> 00:08:42,272
political career.

118
00:08:43,538 --> 00:08:46,238
You know about
my father's illegitimate child?

119
00:08:46,872 --> 00:08:49,905
You knew too, didn't you?

120
00:08:49,905 --> 00:08:51,405
Kang Sun Young!

121
00:08:51,405 --> 00:08:54,705
Isn't that why you care so much about her?
Because she's your sister?

122
00:08:55,705 --> 00:08:57,372
Who did you say?

123
00:09:12,438 --> 00:09:13,672
I have a favor to ask.

124
00:09:13,672 --> 00:09:15,138
I'll handle the investigation properly
from now on.

125
00:09:15,138 --> 00:09:17,805
Does that mean Ki Beom can be released?

126
00:09:17,805 --> 00:09:20,205
[Punish murderer Cha Si Young]
Your man only got a few slaps,

127
00:09:20,205 --> 00:09:23,905
but mine lost his life.

128
00:09:23,905 --> 00:09:26,772
Because of this murderer!

129
00:09:36,572 --> 00:09:38,372
Please just look at this.

130
00:09:46,659 --> 00:09:50,275
[25 years ago]

131
00:10:02,972 --> 00:10:05,605
What if someone sees you here?

132
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:08,838
This child is your blood.

133
00:10:09,905 --> 00:10:12,472
I named her according to your family line.

134
00:10:12,472 --> 00:10:14,205
It's Sun Young.

135
00:10:14,205 --> 00:10:17,772
What's the point of giving a girl
a generational name?

136
00:10:18,472 --> 00:10:20,338
Please put this child
on your family registry.

137
00:10:20,338 --> 00:10:22,305
You dare say that to me?

138
00:10:26,872 --> 00:10:30,305
I treated her nicely, and now
the little brat's getting out of line.

139
00:10:30,305 --> 00:10:32,772
How dare she threaten me like that?

140
00:10:37,538 --> 00:10:38,883
Father,

141
00:10:39,505 --> 00:10:42,638
is Kang Sun Young really your daughter?

142
00:10:43,305 --> 00:10:44,938
Yeah.

143
00:10:46,172 --> 00:10:49,405
Why didn't you tell me sooner?
If I had known earlier...

144
00:10:49,405 --> 00:10:51,172
If you had known, what?

145
00:10:51,172 --> 00:10:55,405
You're trying to say you wouldn't have
made her a single mother?

146
00:10:56,905 --> 00:10:57,972
Father,

147
00:10:57,972 --> 00:11:02,601
if word of your illegitimate child gets out,
the backlash will be huge.

148
00:11:02,601 --> 00:11:04,489
Darn it!

149
00:11:09,105 --> 00:11:10,825
Then

150
00:11:11,465 --> 00:11:13,472
I'll have to accept her.

151
00:11:14,505 --> 00:11:16,872
- Pardon?
- Better we reveal it first

152
00:11:16,872 --> 00:11:19,438
than let them expose us.

153
00:11:20,838 --> 00:11:22,772
You take responsibility

154
00:11:22,772 --> 00:11:24,838
and make things right with Sun Young.

155
00:11:24,838 --> 00:11:25,838
Father!

156
00:11:25,838 --> 00:11:29,472
If you'd behaved yourself,
none of this would've happened.

157
00:11:29,472 --> 00:11:31,472
I thought you caught the serial killer,

158
00:11:31,472 --> 00:11:33,705
but you locked up the wrong guy!

159
00:11:33,705 --> 00:11:36,805
Even if you catch the real killer now,
it'd hardly make up for it.

160
00:11:38,205 --> 00:11:41,605
I can't lift my head
in front of the Minister.

161
00:11:41,605 --> 00:11:43,505
What about her brother?

162
00:11:43,505 --> 00:11:46,038
Oh, he's in Kangseng now.

163
00:11:46,038 --> 00:11:47,605
Get him out of there immediately.

164
00:11:47,605 --> 00:11:49,372
Okay.

165
00:11:49,372 --> 00:11:53,272
Separating her from her brother
will make her easier to control.

166
00:11:53,272 --> 00:11:54,905
Okay.

167
00:11:58,672 --> 00:12:02,238
[Kangseng Daily]

168
00:12:03,538 --> 00:12:05,438
Excuse me.

169
00:12:05,438 --> 00:12:07,972
- Oh, Sun Young!
- Ji Won.

170
00:12:07,972 --> 00:12:10,005
Welcome, I've been waiting.

171
00:12:10,005 --> 00:12:11,038
Oh, hello.

172
00:12:11,038 --> 00:12:12,638
This way, please.

173
00:12:18,805 --> 00:12:20,138
You've got nothing to worry about.

174
00:12:20,138 --> 00:12:22,572
There's no such relationship
between the two of them.

175
00:12:22,572 --> 00:12:24,572
[Kang Sun Young]

176
00:12:25,438 --> 00:12:26,438
Hey.

177
00:12:26,438 --> 00:12:28,472
- Yes?
- That young woman.

178
00:12:28,472 --> 00:12:29,472
Yeah.

179
00:12:29,472 --> 00:12:30,972
Is she acquainted with Ms. Seo?

180
00:12:30,972 --> 00:12:33,472
- Yeah.
- How do they know each other?

181
00:12:33,472 --> 00:12:36,138
If I had to say, they're like real sisters.

182
00:12:36,138 --> 00:12:37,772
What?

183
00:12:43,538 --> 00:12:48,272
While the trial of Mr. Im, the suspect
in the Kangseng Serial Murder Case

184
00:12:48,272 --> 00:12:51,038
that claimed 7th victims, is underway,

185
00:12:51,038 --> 00:12:54,538
another murder using the same
method has occurred,

186
00:12:54,538 --> 00:12:58,405
forcing the trial to come to a complete halt.

187
00:12:58,405 --> 00:13:00,238
With the emergence of a new crime,

188
00:13:00,238 --> 00:13:03,572
the possibility has been raised
that Mr. Im may not be the real killer.

189
00:13:03,572 --> 00:13:04,705
Nevertheless,

190
00:13:04,705 --> 00:13:06,972
[Muwon District Court]
the prosecution insists that

191
00:13:06,972 --> 00:13:09,838
Mr. Im is responsible for the 7th murder

192
00:13:09,838 --> 00:13:13,705
and has stated that
they will amend the indictment

193
00:13:13,705 --> 00:13:16,738
and continue the trial on that charge.

194
00:13:21,872 --> 00:13:24,305
Yes, this is Seo Ji Won from Kangseng Daily.

195
00:13:26,272 --> 00:13:27,938
Hello?

196
00:13:29,005 --> 00:13:31,272
This is Im Ji Hye.

197
00:13:32,172 --> 00:13:34,172
I'm Seok Man's older sister.

198
00:13:39,538 --> 00:13:41,538
The victim found yesterday was Hong Yeo Jin,

199
00:13:41,538 --> 00:13:43,272
26 years old.

200
00:13:43,272 --> 00:13:45,505
[Investigation Report]
As expected, strangled with stockings.

201
00:13:45,505 --> 00:13:48,305
And considering the various methods used,

202
00:13:48,305 --> 00:13:51,038
it's clearly the work of the serial killer.

203
00:13:51,038 --> 00:13:52,638
Okay.

204
00:13:54,738 --> 00:14:00,072
Oh, as for the commendation,
I personally apologized to the Minister.

205
00:14:00,072 --> 00:14:02,038
What did he say?

206
00:14:02,038 --> 00:14:04,538
I said we would return
everything we received.

207
00:14:04,538 --> 00:14:08,038
Well, we did catch at least one murderer.

208
00:14:08,038 --> 00:14:11,105
And he said as long as
we catch the serial killer soon,

209
00:14:11,105 --> 00:14:13,321
there won't be any problem.

210
00:14:13,321 --> 00:14:14,477
Alright, sir.

211
00:14:15,405 --> 00:14:18,438
And you've worked so hard all this time.

212
00:14:18,438 --> 00:14:20,538
You should return to your jurisdiction now.

213
00:14:26,572 --> 00:14:30,072
Looks like you never intended to actually
catch the killer in the first place, right?

214
00:14:30,072 --> 00:14:34,138
Your chief and I both agree that
it would be better for all of us

215
00:14:34,138 --> 00:14:38,572
to conduct separate investigations
rather than work together.

216
00:14:38,572 --> 00:14:40,605
And they're asking for you
to be sent back quickly.

217
00:14:43,138 --> 00:14:45,405
I understand what you're saying.

218
00:14:45,405 --> 00:14:47,172
Okay, then.

219
00:15:04,705 --> 00:15:07,138
Do you think he'll just go back quietly?

220
00:15:07,138 --> 00:15:09,772
If that punk catches the killer first,

221
00:15:09,772 --> 00:15:11,272
then you guys

222
00:15:11,272 --> 00:15:14,805
will be demoted, transferred,
and your careers will be over.

223
00:15:14,805 --> 00:15:16,772
Do you understand what I mean?

224
00:15:16,772 --> 00:15:19,472
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, we'll keep that in mind, sir.

225
00:15:20,372 --> 00:15:23,938
Then get out there
and catch the killer, you punks!

226
00:15:23,938 --> 00:15:26,205
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, understood, sir!

227
00:15:31,338 --> 00:15:34,438
- What do we do?
- I don't know, you idiot.

228
00:15:34,438 --> 00:15:35,938
Well, chief...

229
00:15:35,938 --> 00:15:37,205
What?

230
00:15:37,205 --> 00:15:38,272
I need to tell you something.

231
00:15:38,272 --> 00:15:39,872
What is it?

232
00:15:41,105 --> 00:15:42,372
Well...

233
00:15:42,372 --> 00:15:44,105
Spit it out!

234
00:15:46,857 --> 00:15:48,745
Darn it!

235
00:15:50,105 --> 00:15:52,005
You sure it was here, you punk?

236
00:15:52,005 --> 00:15:53,472
Could it be that you've remembered it wrong?

237
00:15:53,472 --> 00:15:55,638
Yes, I'm sure.

238
00:15:56,438 --> 00:15:58,505
Then why did you do something
you weren't told to do?

239
00:15:58,505 --> 00:16:00,338
I'm sorry, sir.

240
00:16:00,338 --> 00:16:04,372
Seeing Hye Jin's family
made me feel bad, so...

241
00:16:04,372 --> 00:16:06,072
This is insane.

242
00:16:06,072 --> 00:16:09,938
Now what am I supposed to tell Mr. Cha?

243
00:16:11,005 --> 00:16:12,605
Could it be

244
00:16:13,505 --> 00:16:15,338
Kang Tae Joo?

245
00:16:15,338 --> 00:16:17,005
How would Kang Tae Joo know about this?

246
00:16:17,005 --> 00:16:18,438
These two...

247
00:16:18,438 --> 00:16:20,105
That punk must have been tailing him.

248
00:16:20,105 --> 00:16:22,305
It's not one of these two.

249
00:16:22,305 --> 00:16:24,372
Oh, come on.

250
00:16:24,372 --> 00:16:27,172
But the thing is, Detective Kang

251
00:16:27,172 --> 00:16:28,838
did say something strange.

252
00:16:28,838 --> 00:16:30,538
What did he say?

253
00:16:30,538 --> 00:16:32,305
I'm telling you,

254
00:16:32,938 --> 00:16:36,905
I'll catch him when the whole country
is in fear of a serial killer.

255
00:16:36,905 --> 00:16:38,105
When would that be?

256
00:16:38,105 --> 00:16:40,872
When murders are happening every day.

257
00:16:41,572 --> 00:16:43,972
Is that even possible?

258
00:16:43,972 --> 00:16:45,838
The killer is getting addicted to killing.

259
00:16:45,838 --> 00:16:49,538
At this rate, he'll kill
like it's a daily routine.

260
00:16:49,538 --> 00:16:51,838
That's when we'll catch him.

261
00:16:53,472 --> 00:16:54,622
But

262
00:16:55,401 --> 00:16:57,372
even if you want to catch him then,

263
00:16:57,372 --> 00:16:59,705
you still need to find out who the killer is.

264
00:17:01,105 --> 00:17:03,238
I've got ways to catch the killer.

265
00:17:06,805 --> 00:17:10,038
Kang Tae Joo did say that?

266
00:17:12,405 --> 00:17:16,805
He might have already found the killer.

267
00:17:20,505 --> 00:17:22,105
[Muil Inn]

268
00:17:22,105 --> 00:17:25,059
Detective Jang and Detective Do
didn't seem to know.

269
00:17:26,005 --> 00:17:28,272
Then there's only Cha Si Young.

270
00:17:29,072 --> 00:17:31,472
We can only find out where Hye Jin is

271
00:17:31,472 --> 00:17:34,072
if he talks and tells us everything.

272
00:17:35,205 --> 00:17:37,438
Did you tell them what I said?

273
00:17:37,438 --> 00:17:41,705
Yes, I told them
you might have found the killer.

274
00:17:41,705 --> 00:17:44,705
But why tell them that?

275
00:17:44,705 --> 00:17:48,305
If that reaches his ears,
he'll try to test me at least once.

276
00:17:48,305 --> 00:17:52,172
If I approach Cha Si Young first now,
it'll be too obvious.

277
00:17:56,672 --> 00:17:58,772
Don't worry.

278
00:17:58,772 --> 00:18:01,172
I'll find Hye Jin somehow.

279
00:18:02,772 --> 00:18:04,405
Okay.

280
00:18:06,805 --> 00:18:11,405
Did you really meet Seok Man
in Kangseng on the day of the murder?

281
00:18:11,405 --> 00:18:13,038
Yes.

282
00:18:14,405 --> 00:18:18,405
Then why did Seok Man try to hide that?

283
00:18:18,405 --> 00:18:20,238
He didn't mention that?

284
00:18:20,238 --> 00:18:22,438
No, and that's why he became
even more suspicious.

285
00:18:22,438 --> 00:18:25,438
Because he hid his whereabouts that day.

286
00:18:30,505 --> 00:18:32,938
What an idiot...

287
00:18:34,243 --> 00:18:35,672
[September 22nd,
the day of the seventh case]

288
00:18:35,672 --> 00:18:37,272
Here,

289
00:18:37,972 --> 00:18:40,472
take this to your boss.

290
00:18:41,605 --> 00:18:44,038
You should treat him and his wife well.

291
00:18:44,038 --> 00:18:46,672
There aren't many like them, okay?

292
00:18:52,005 --> 00:18:53,838
Are you going to stay mad until I leave?

293
00:18:53,838 --> 00:18:55,905
You didn't even bring Tae Ho.

294
00:18:56,705 --> 00:18:59,238
Then I'll come on Tae Ho's birthday, okay?

295
00:18:59,238 --> 00:19:00,672
I'll give him the present then.

296
00:19:00,672 --> 00:19:04,205
We won't be home that day.
We're going to my in-laws'.

297
00:19:04,205 --> 00:19:06,072
Then I'll go too.

298
00:19:06,072 --> 00:19:07,705
Seok Man.

299
00:19:09,505 --> 00:19:11,689
My in-laws

300
00:19:11,689 --> 00:19:13,905
don't like you seeing Tae Ho.

301
00:19:15,172 --> 00:19:18,338
Because he keeps copying you.

302
00:19:19,438 --> 00:19:21,072
Copying me?

303
00:19:21,072 --> 00:19:24,838
He keeps imitating your walk.

304
00:19:28,505 --> 00:19:30,472
That's why I came today.

305
00:19:30,472 --> 00:19:32,872
Since I might not be able to
see you on his birthday.

306
00:19:36,238 --> 00:19:39,872
Actually, I have a lot to do too. Good then.

307
00:19:39,872 --> 00:19:41,972
I can just work that day.

308
00:19:44,238 --> 00:19:47,172
[Mini Race Car]
Here, this is for Tae Ho's birthday.

309
00:19:49,938 --> 00:19:51,772
I'll give it to him.

310
00:19:54,272 --> 00:19:58,005
Please don't tell my husband
that you met me today.

311
00:19:58,005 --> 00:20:01,705
My mother-in-law is sick,
but I said I had to work and came out.

312
00:20:02,438 --> 00:20:04,105
Alright.

313
00:20:04,105 --> 00:20:06,205
I won't tell anyone.

314
00:20:07,038 --> 00:20:10,338
I'm tight-lipped. Don't worry.

315
00:20:11,305 --> 00:20:15,072
But how could he not even tell the police?

316
00:20:15,072 --> 00:20:16,338
That's just how he is.

317
00:20:16,338 --> 00:20:18,305
He really has no flexibility.

318
00:20:18,305 --> 00:20:22,472
Yeah, he's sticking to his promise to you,
even though he can't even provide an alibi.

319
00:20:24,172 --> 00:20:25,805
Then,

320
00:20:26,538 --> 00:20:29,705
what time did you part
at the station that day?

321
00:20:30,572 --> 00:20:32,472
It was 10:30 p.m.

322
00:20:32,472 --> 00:20:34,538
I took the last train.

323
00:20:34,538 --> 00:20:36,038
10:30 p.m.?

324
00:20:36,038 --> 00:20:37,038
10:30 p.m.?

325
00:20:37,038 --> 00:20:39,772
Yeah, that's the estimated time of the crime.

326
00:20:39,772 --> 00:20:42,638
So does that mean
Im Seok Man's alibi is confirmed?

327
00:20:43,472 --> 00:20:45,272
It's only an estimate.

328
00:20:45,272 --> 00:20:49,238
There's still a possibility
Lee Joo Hee died after 11 p.m.

329
00:20:49,238 --> 00:20:51,705
Why are you so certain
Im Seok Man is the killer?

330
00:20:51,705 --> 00:20:53,438
There's more than just
one piece of circumstantial evidence.

331
00:20:53,438 --> 00:20:55,038
Even the radioactive isotope test results...

332
00:20:55,038 --> 00:20:57,872
That! Are you sure that test is reliable?

333
00:20:57,872 --> 00:21:01,005
It has never been used
as evidence in court before, right?

334
00:21:01,005 --> 00:21:03,238
There's always a first time for everything.

335
00:21:06,172 --> 00:21:07,972
Then let's verify it.

336
00:21:08,805 --> 00:21:09,838
Verify what?

337
00:21:09,838 --> 00:21:14,038
You said that test can reveal a suspect's
living environment and habits, right?

338
00:21:14,038 --> 00:21:18,005
Then wouldn't people with similar lifestyles
produce similar results?

339
00:21:18,005 --> 00:21:20,005
Let's just test that.

340
00:21:24,105 --> 00:21:25,372
[Ironworks]
What are you talking about?

341
00:21:25,372 --> 00:21:27,272
You want to pluck my pubic hair?

342
00:21:27,272 --> 00:21:31,205
Because you live with Seok Man

343
00:21:31,205 --> 00:21:32,872
and do similar work as him.

344
00:21:32,872 --> 00:21:35,672
So your test results could
end up looking very similar to his.

345
00:21:35,672 --> 00:21:39,072
I mean, it's good we might
clear Seok Man's name,

346
00:21:39,072 --> 00:21:43,372
but what if this ends up
putting him in the frame?

347
00:21:43,372 --> 00:21:45,572
His alibi is solid, so that shouldn't happen.

348
00:21:45,572 --> 00:21:47,505
Right.

349
00:21:47,505 --> 00:21:49,838
Honey, what should we do?

350
00:21:49,838 --> 00:21:52,738
Should I take my underwear off?

351
00:21:57,805 --> 00:21:59,938
Yeah, honey! Take it off!

352
00:21:59,938 --> 00:22:01,372
Let's save Seok Man while we're at it.

353
00:22:01,372 --> 00:22:02,438
- Let's go over there.
- You're right!

354
00:22:02,438 --> 00:22:04,538
- I'll take it off!
- Okay, let's hurry.

355
00:22:04,538 --> 00:22:06,138
- I'll take the sample now.
- Here?

356
00:22:06,138 --> 00:22:08,072
- Now?
- Hold on...

357
00:22:08,072 --> 00:22:09,772
- This...
- Take it off.

358
00:22:09,772 --> 00:22:11,738
- Right here...
- Just pull it out!

359
00:22:11,738 --> 00:22:14,338
Fine, I'll do it myself. Get out of the way.

360
00:22:14,338 --> 00:22:15,538
Do we just fill this up?

361
00:22:15,538 --> 00:22:17,805
What do you mean fill it up?

362
00:22:17,805 --> 00:22:19,105
Hurry up!

363
00:22:19,105 --> 00:22:20,305
Jeez, wait.

364
00:22:20,305 --> 00:22:22,505
[Korea Atomic Energy Research Institute]

365
00:22:25,405 --> 00:22:26,672
Oh, surprising.

366
00:22:26,672 --> 00:22:30,705
This one also shows the same elemental
distribution as the suspect's sample.

367
00:22:30,705 --> 00:22:32,489
And besides,

368
00:22:32,489 --> 00:22:34,601
the margin of error is even lower

369
00:22:34,601 --> 00:22:36,705
than the previous suspect's.

370
00:22:37,638 --> 00:22:42,372
Have you finally found
the real serial killer this time?

371
00:22:42,372 --> 00:22:44,172
What exactly is this test?

372
00:22:44,172 --> 00:22:45,905
Can different people show

373
00:22:45,905 --> 00:22:51,005
identical results if they have
similar jobs or environments?

374
00:22:51,005 --> 00:22:52,605
Of course.

375
00:22:55,305 --> 00:22:59,005
So even if I identified the wrong suspect,

376
00:22:59,005 --> 00:23:02,405
the results could still match?

377
00:23:03,972 --> 00:23:08,405
If the premise is flawed,
even with matching results,

378
00:23:08,405 --> 00:23:10,405
you can't consider them the killer.

379
00:23:13,505 --> 00:23:15,672
Was it a wrong premise?

380
00:23:15,672 --> 00:23:19,593
That's something you'd know
better than anyone, Detective.

381
00:23:37,005 --> 00:23:39,972
The reason I suspected Im Seok Man was...

382
00:23:42,338 --> 00:23:46,038
First, he was seen
at the Lee Joo Hee crime scene.

383
00:23:47,238 --> 00:23:49,705
Then there was Ki Beom's handkerchief.

384
00:23:49,705 --> 00:23:51,472
I found this purse.

385
00:23:51,472 --> 00:23:54,505
Then you are the one
who left the purse in the bookstore?

386
00:23:54,505 --> 00:23:57,072
Park Ae Sook's purse was the second clue.

387
00:24:00,205 --> 00:24:02,238
No,

388
00:24:02,238 --> 00:24:06,805
those two are connected to the serial killer,
so they should be excluded.

389
00:24:06,805 --> 00:24:08,638
And also...

390
00:24:08,638 --> 00:24:10,072
I remembered what happened that day.

391
00:24:10,072 --> 00:24:13,138
He was limping, like he was injured.

392
00:24:13,138 --> 00:24:14,838
It's true!

393
00:24:17,905 --> 00:24:20,272
You like Sun Young, huh?

394
00:24:20,272 --> 00:24:21,505
That's why you hate Ki Beom?

395
00:24:21,505 --> 00:24:23,805
I liked her first!

396
00:24:23,805 --> 00:24:26,205
I said I liked her first.

397
00:24:26,838 --> 00:24:29,172
Even though he knew I liked her...

398
00:24:49,805 --> 00:24:51,405
Sun Young!

399
00:25:03,705 --> 00:25:05,938
You haven't changed at all.

400
00:25:06,572 --> 00:25:09,805
You're the same as when you were little.

401
00:25:12,538 --> 00:25:14,438
Do I know you?

402
00:25:15,872 --> 00:25:17,472
I'm your father.

403
00:25:38,205 --> 00:25:42,305
I've kept this photo all my life.

404
00:25:44,305 --> 00:25:45,505
But why now?

405
00:25:45,505 --> 00:25:47,241
Back then,

406
00:25:47,241 --> 00:25:49,638
your mother and I

407
00:25:49,638 --> 00:25:51,772
both had families.

408
00:25:56,205 --> 00:26:00,372
I only recently learned

409
00:26:00,372 --> 00:26:02,538
you are pregnant and alone.

410
00:26:03,405 --> 00:26:05,405
It might be late,

411
00:26:05,405 --> 00:26:09,572
but I thought this is when you might

412
00:26:09,572 --> 00:26:11,372
need me.

413
00:26:14,538 --> 00:26:19,272
From now on, live as my daughter.

414
00:26:21,572 --> 00:26:22,953
Let me

415
00:26:23,817 --> 00:26:26,138
protect you and your child.

416
00:26:34,572 --> 00:26:37,705
By the way, why is Cha Si Young so quiet?

417
00:26:37,705 --> 00:26:40,605
Did Jang Myeong Do not pass on the message?

418
00:26:41,638 --> 00:26:46,172
He probably didn't move
Hye Jin's body himself.

419
00:26:46,172 --> 00:26:48,672
If he had someone do it for him...

420
00:26:48,672 --> 00:26:50,738
Hey, Tae Joo!

421
00:26:51,605 --> 00:26:53,605
Hey, you punk. It's been so long!

422
00:26:53,605 --> 00:26:56,005
I saw you at the hospital with Si Young...

423
00:26:58,979 --> 00:27:00,605
Darn it!

424
00:27:00,605 --> 00:27:02,605
What was that?

425
00:27:02,605 --> 00:27:05,289
I thought you'd come at me again like before.

426
00:27:05,289 --> 00:27:07,238
Darn it!

427
00:27:07,238 --> 00:27:09,738
That was ages ago!

428
00:27:13,105 --> 00:27:17,172
Get to the point.
Don't pretend you're happy to see me.

429
00:27:17,172 --> 00:27:18,972
Come with me.

430
00:27:19,838 --> 00:27:22,705
- Why would I go with you?
- You've never been to my place, right?

431
00:27:22,705 --> 00:27:24,638
- I'll cover everything today.
- Have I lost my mind?

432
00:27:24,638 --> 00:27:26,738
You think I'd sit down and drink with you?

433
00:27:26,738 --> 00:27:28,372
Tae Joo!

434
00:27:28,372 --> 00:27:29,372
Tae Joo, just once...

435
00:27:29,372 --> 00:27:30,372
- Just go with me once.
- Let go!

436
00:27:30,372 --> 00:27:31,505
I'm begging you, just this once!

437
00:27:31,505 --> 00:27:33,038
- Let go, you punk!
- Please, just once.

438
00:27:33,038 --> 00:27:35,338
- Just this once, please!
- Let go!

439
00:27:35,338 --> 00:27:38,338
Just go with me once, just once!

440
00:27:44,005 --> 00:27:45,838
What should we do?

441
00:27:45,838 --> 00:27:48,272
What do you mean? Just carry it.

442
00:27:54,338 --> 00:27:56,572
I'm begging you, just once!

443
00:27:56,572 --> 00:27:58,905
Park Sang Beom, so it's you.

444
00:27:58,905 --> 00:28:00,472
Huh? Just once...

445
00:28:00,472 --> 00:28:02,572
Just once, please!

446
00:28:07,105 --> 00:28:08,305
This is a bit awkward.

447
00:28:08,305 --> 00:28:11,305
We're not exactly the type to sit
and share a table like this, huh?

448
00:28:12,172 --> 00:28:13,972
Get to the point.

449
00:28:21,272 --> 00:28:23,805
I'm so sorry about what happened back then.

450
00:28:24,738 --> 00:28:27,905
I was... I was really immature.

451
00:28:27,905 --> 00:28:30,072
Can you forgive me?

452
00:28:30,805 --> 00:28:33,772
Why are you doing something
you normally wouldn't do?

453
00:28:33,772 --> 00:28:36,338
I'm so sorry, Tae Joo.

454
00:28:42,305 --> 00:28:45,372
Sang Beom, give us a moment.

455
00:28:45,372 --> 00:28:48,172
Oh, sure. You guys talk.

456
00:28:51,772 --> 00:28:54,405
Sang Beom didn't do anything wrong.

457
00:28:54,405 --> 00:28:56,372
I was the one who told him to do it.

458
00:28:58,605 --> 00:29:01,172
About everything I've done to you so far,

459
00:29:02,238 --> 00:29:04,172
I was wrong.

460
00:29:06,605 --> 00:29:08,205
I'm not asking you to forgive me.

461
00:29:08,205 --> 00:29:12,472
But if it's ever possible,

462
00:29:12,472 --> 00:29:15,972
I really want to stay friends with you.

463
00:29:19,938 --> 00:29:22,038
Just tell me what you're doing this for.

464
00:29:23,072 --> 00:29:24,329
Our bond

465
00:29:25,417 --> 00:29:27,472
is not ordinary.

466
00:29:28,372 --> 00:29:30,905
In a way, we're closer than blood.

467
00:29:30,905 --> 00:29:32,845
Have you been drinking during the day?

468
00:29:32,845 --> 00:29:35,238
Why are you talking in circles?
Say it straight.

469
00:29:35,238 --> 00:29:37,305
Sun Young is my sister, you know.

470
00:29:43,172 --> 00:29:44,405
What nonsense is that?

471
00:29:44,405 --> 00:29:46,438
My father acknowledged it.

472
00:29:48,172 --> 00:29:51,505
Why do you think your mother
named her Sun Young?

473
00:29:51,505 --> 00:29:55,138
Jun Young, Si Young, Sun Young.

474
00:29:56,105 --> 00:29:59,505
She must have known she would be
added to Father's family registry someday.

475
00:30:03,805 --> 00:30:06,405
Your sister has a good older brother.

476
00:30:17,638 --> 00:30:19,238
You're lying.

477
00:30:24,372 --> 00:30:26,005
Fine.

478
00:30:27,272 --> 00:30:29,238
Let's say that's true.

479
00:30:29,238 --> 00:30:31,172
So what now?

480
00:30:31,172 --> 00:30:32,713
He should've played father
when she was young.

481
00:30:32,713 --> 00:30:34,472
What now that she's all grown up?

482
00:30:34,472 --> 00:30:35,905
Does having kids make him a father?

483
00:30:35,905 --> 00:30:37,129
My father

484
00:30:37,801 --> 00:30:40,105
wants Sun Young on the family registry.

485
00:30:43,472 --> 00:30:45,638
What gave him the right?

486
00:30:45,638 --> 00:30:48,572
Listen, that man does
whatever he puts his mind to.

487
00:30:48,572 --> 00:30:51,605
He might have already met Sun Young!

488
00:30:51,605 --> 00:30:54,338
You crazy punk!

489
00:30:54,338 --> 00:30:56,772
You should've stopped it somehow!

490
00:30:56,772 --> 00:30:58,372
How could you and Sun Young...

491
00:30:58,372 --> 00:31:00,872
How could she be connected to the man
who killed her husband?

492
00:31:00,872 --> 00:31:04,638
Why are you and your family so cruel to her?

493
00:31:05,338 --> 00:31:07,438
Please help me.

494
00:31:07,438 --> 00:31:09,405
Help you?

495
00:31:09,405 --> 00:31:10,857
Me?

496
00:31:14,638 --> 00:31:16,805
So this is what it was.

497
00:31:16,805 --> 00:31:19,438
All that "I'm sorry" talk was for this.

498
00:31:19,438 --> 00:31:21,038
Tae Joo!

499
00:31:21,672 --> 00:31:24,872
We're basically brothers now.

500
00:31:24,872 --> 00:31:26,638
I admit all my past wrongs.

501
00:31:26,638 --> 00:31:29,038
I'm sorry for how I treated you
and for all the hurt I've caused.

502
00:31:29,038 --> 00:31:30,072
Shut up, you punk!

503
00:31:30,072 --> 00:31:31,138
I don't need any of this.

504
00:31:31,138 --> 00:31:34,538
Cut the crap, and I'll tell you
what you need to do from now on.

505
00:31:34,538 --> 00:31:36,672
Don't ever let Sun Young know

506
00:31:36,672 --> 00:31:39,005
you're her brother!

507
00:32:22,405 --> 00:32:25,238
Why are you doing this to me?

508
00:32:33,238 --> 00:32:35,005
Just how...

509
00:32:35,005 --> 00:32:37,905
Just how messed up was your life!

510
00:32:37,905 --> 00:32:42,505
Even in death, you splash filth
on your own children!

511
00:32:49,638 --> 00:32:51,738
Sun Young...

512
00:32:54,405 --> 00:32:56,938
What about Sun Young?

513
00:32:57,605 --> 00:33:00,105
What is our Sun Young supposed to do!

514
00:33:02,705 --> 00:33:04,705
How far are you going to

515
00:33:05,438 --> 00:33:08,072
drag that poor girl down?

516
00:34:02,305 --> 00:34:04,238
What are you doing right now?

517
00:34:04,238 --> 00:34:06,305
Go somewhere else for a while.

518
00:34:06,305 --> 00:34:07,338
You know Mr. Kim, right?

519
00:34:07,338 --> 00:34:09,038
Mr. Kim is in Busan now.

520
00:34:09,038 --> 00:34:12,838
He's there with his wife.
Go there and clear your head.

521
00:34:12,838 --> 00:34:14,438
How am I supposed to be in the mood for that?

522
00:34:14,438 --> 00:34:15,438
We haven't even found Hye Jin yet...

523
00:34:15,438 --> 00:34:17,305
Just do as you're told!

524
00:34:23,572 --> 00:34:25,172
Tae Joo.

525
00:34:26,205 --> 00:34:27,805
Please.

526
00:34:29,572 --> 00:34:31,305
Just tell me why, at least.

527
00:34:31,305 --> 00:34:32,905
Later.

528
00:34:37,672 --> 00:34:40,605
Is this about the man
who claims to be my father?

529
00:34:40,605 --> 00:34:42,238
What?

530
00:34:45,205 --> 00:34:47,005
Did that punk come here?

531
00:34:47,005 --> 00:34:48,638
He came earlier this afternoon.

532
00:34:50,405 --> 00:34:51,605
What did he say?

533
00:34:51,605 --> 00:34:53,417
He said

534
00:34:53,417 --> 00:34:55,938
he wants to carry out his responsibility
as my father, even now.

535
00:34:57,305 --> 00:34:59,172
What a load of nonsense.

536
00:35:02,205 --> 00:35:05,838
Do you hate that I finally have a father?

537
00:35:05,838 --> 00:35:08,438
It's not that.

538
00:35:08,438 --> 00:35:10,638
I'm flustered too!

539
00:35:11,972 --> 00:35:13,545
But

540
00:35:14,409 --> 00:35:16,638
at the same time, it felt reassuring.

541
00:35:19,238 --> 00:35:24,005
What if the child gets judged
for not having a father?

542
00:35:24,972 --> 00:35:28,105
What if they get rejected at school
for being the child of a single mother?

543
00:35:28,105 --> 00:35:29,505
You think I don't worry about that?

544
00:35:29,505 --> 00:35:32,238
Why are you worrying about that? I'm here!

545
00:35:32,238 --> 00:35:36,538
I'll be both the father
and the uncle to that child. Why?

546
00:35:36,538 --> 00:35:37,905
That punk is not acceptable!

547
00:35:37,905 --> 00:35:40,405
He's not someone you can trust!

548
00:35:41,938 --> 00:35:44,172
He's no good as a person.

549
00:35:45,472 --> 00:35:47,105
Why?

550
00:35:48,438 --> 00:35:50,038
Why do you say that?

551
00:35:50,772 --> 00:35:52,172
He's still my father.

552
00:35:52,172 --> 00:35:54,572
Since when is he your father?

553
00:35:54,572 --> 00:35:57,038
Does that word come out so easily?

554
00:36:01,838 --> 00:36:03,572
Hey,

555
00:36:03,572 --> 00:36:05,305
Sun Young.

556
00:36:10,972 --> 00:36:15,138
Just this once, do what I say.

557
00:36:15,138 --> 00:36:17,238
Okay?

558
00:36:17,238 --> 00:36:18,838
I'm begging you.

559
00:36:26,138 --> 00:36:29,738
I already contacted Mr. Kim,
so he'll meet you at the station.

560
00:36:29,738 --> 00:36:33,005
How long do I have to stay there?

561
00:36:33,005 --> 00:36:35,872
Wait until I contact you. Okay?

562
00:36:37,872 --> 00:36:39,505
Go ahead.

563
00:36:40,238 --> 00:36:42,005
Get inside now.

564
00:36:44,638 --> 00:36:47,138
Call me when you arrive.

565
00:36:47,138 --> 00:36:48,738
Okay?

566
00:36:54,072 --> 00:36:56,138
Contact me as soon as you get there.

567
00:36:57,872 --> 00:36:59,838
Make sure you eat well.

568
00:37:01,738 --> 00:37:06,505
[Muwon]

569
00:37:23,872 --> 00:37:25,738
Sun Young,

570
00:37:27,505 --> 00:37:30,705
you're not alone.

571
00:37:32,972 --> 00:37:36,472
Your father will protect you.

572
00:37:36,472 --> 00:37:38,272
Father?

573
00:37:40,505 --> 00:37:43,405
Mom, Mom...

574
00:37:44,872 --> 00:37:47,438
Mom, Mom!

575
00:38:05,738 --> 00:38:09,372
[National Assemblyman Cha Mu Jin]

576
00:38:16,675 --> 00:38:18,238
[Muil Inn]

577
00:38:18,238 --> 00:38:20,305
Hey, your sister hasn't arrived.

578
00:38:20,305 --> 00:38:22,338
Are you sure she took the train?

579
00:38:25,472 --> 00:38:27,072
Tae Joo!

580
00:38:31,272 --> 00:38:34,372
Where is Sun Young? You know, don't you?

581
00:38:34,372 --> 00:38:36,572
She's with Father now.

582
00:38:36,572 --> 00:38:38,672
She came on her own. Of her own will.

583
00:38:38,672 --> 00:38:41,005
I told you to stop her somehow!

584
00:38:45,805 --> 00:38:48,438
No wonder I felt drawn to her
every time I saw her.

585
00:38:48,438 --> 00:38:51,105
I didn't know what that feeling
meant at the time,

586
00:38:51,105 --> 00:38:53,372
but I understand now.

587
00:38:53,372 --> 00:38:55,405
It was blood calling.

588
00:38:57,938 --> 00:38:59,605
Tae Joo,

589
00:38:59,605 --> 00:39:01,705
I'm not like my brother.

590
00:39:02,705 --> 00:39:05,372
I'll be a truly good brother to Sun Young.

591
00:39:05,372 --> 00:39:08,205
And you, who share
the same blood as Sun Young,

592
00:39:08,205 --> 00:39:10,338
are basically my brother too.

593
00:39:10,338 --> 00:39:13,005
Are you freaking kidding me, you punk?

594
00:39:13,705 --> 00:39:15,705
Yeah, you probably

595
00:39:15,705 --> 00:39:19,505
can't forgive what I did to you.

596
00:39:19,505 --> 00:39:21,138
But I'll make it up in my own way.

597
00:39:21,138 --> 00:39:22,838
Make it up?

598
00:39:23,638 --> 00:39:25,838
- How?
- Tell me whatever you want.

599
00:39:25,838 --> 00:39:28,272
What? You want me to transfer you to Seoul?

600
00:39:28,272 --> 00:39:30,272
You want me to promote you?

601
00:39:30,272 --> 00:39:31,872
- Are you serious?
- Then,

602
00:39:31,872 --> 00:39:34,438
if you catch the serial killer this time,

603
00:39:34,438 --> 00:39:37,257
I'll give you whatever you want,
a special promotion and everything.

604
00:39:37,257 --> 00:39:38,605
How about that?

605
00:39:40,138 --> 00:39:41,772
Give Hye Jin back.

606
00:39:44,172 --> 00:39:45,238
Who?

607
00:39:45,238 --> 00:39:48,572
That girl you told someone
to bury for you, Hye Jin.

608
00:39:48,572 --> 00:39:50,805
She's Sun Young's favorite student.

609
00:39:55,538 --> 00:39:56,572
I don't know what you're talking about.

610
00:39:56,572 --> 00:39:57,705
Just let me find Hye Jin!

611
00:39:57,705 --> 00:40:00,305
Then I'll let go of everything you did to me.

612
00:40:00,305 --> 00:40:02,838
All those ugly things between us,
I'll forget them.

613
00:40:02,838 --> 00:40:03,972
I have no idea about anything.

614
00:40:03,972 --> 00:40:06,905
- Cha Si Young!
- I said I don't know, darn it!

615
00:40:11,038 --> 00:40:13,072
I'll keep it to myself.

616
00:40:13,072 --> 00:40:15,005
I'll take it to my grave. It never happened.

617
00:40:15,005 --> 00:40:17,272
Nothing will come back to hurt you!

618
00:40:24,638 --> 00:40:26,438
So this is what it's about?

619
00:40:27,605 --> 00:40:29,353
All that talk about finding the killer,

620
00:40:29,353 --> 00:40:32,072
saying the more bodies turn up
at the same time, the better.

621
00:40:33,238 --> 00:40:37,238
You were making me
dig that girl out with my own hands?

622
00:40:37,238 --> 00:40:40,938
Wow, Kang Tae Joo, you're clever, huh?

623
00:40:40,938 --> 00:40:43,805
So all that killer-catching talk
was all a lie, huh?

624
00:40:43,805 --> 00:40:47,705
But seriously, I really don't know
where that girl is.

625
00:40:47,705 --> 00:40:49,338
I've got proof.

626
00:40:57,872 --> 00:40:59,472
Check it yourself.

627
00:41:02,305 --> 00:41:06,372
I compared the hair found
at the 5th crime scene with the suspect's.

628
00:41:06,372 --> 00:41:07,465
It has a lower error rate than Im Seok Man's

629
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:08,905
from the 7th case.

630
00:41:08,905 --> 00:41:10,538
Do you believe me now?

631
00:41:15,272 --> 00:41:16,905
So you really found him.

632
00:41:16,905 --> 00:41:17,972
Just let me find the girl.

633
00:41:17,972 --> 00:41:19,305
As for that killer,

634
00:41:19,305 --> 00:41:21,338
credit the arrest to you.

635
00:41:26,305 --> 00:41:27,938
Wait.

636
00:41:28,605 --> 00:41:31,072
Okay, let's say I buried
that girl as you said.

637
00:41:31,072 --> 00:41:34,872
But what if you change your story
after I help you find her?

638
00:41:34,872 --> 00:41:37,805
If you don't trust me, trust Sun Young.

639
00:41:37,805 --> 00:41:39,838
You're her brother, aren't you?

640
00:41:40,572 --> 00:41:43,805
I also don't want Sun Young
to hate you anymore, either.

641
00:41:43,805 --> 00:41:47,205
Because that would be more painful
for her than anyone.

642
00:41:47,205 --> 00:41:49,838
Fine, let's just say what's done is done.

643
00:41:49,838 --> 00:41:53,738
But this is something you have to fix, okay?

644
00:41:55,205 --> 00:41:57,405
If you're really her brother.

645
00:41:58,638 --> 00:42:00,238
Cha Si Young.

646
00:42:01,605 --> 00:42:03,113
Fine.

647
00:42:03,113 --> 00:42:05,438
I'll help you find the girl.

648
00:42:06,405 --> 00:42:08,605
But I decide when.

649
00:42:09,805 --> 00:42:11,705
What do you mean?

650
00:42:11,705 --> 00:42:13,305
Someone said it,

651
00:42:13,305 --> 00:42:16,072
catching the killer now
can hardly make up for it.

652
00:42:16,072 --> 00:42:20,105
Yeah, the Kangseng Serial Murder Case
is starting to lose attention.

653
00:42:20,105 --> 00:42:23,638
We need something
that grabs the public attention again.

654
00:42:23,638 --> 00:42:25,605
Don't tell me...

655
00:42:25,605 --> 00:42:28,638
On the day the next murder happens,

656
00:42:28,638 --> 00:42:31,838
that's when the girl will be revealed too.

657
00:42:31,838 --> 00:42:34,638
Two bodies, back-to-back in a single day.

658
00:42:34,638 --> 00:42:36,272
Got it?

659
00:43:02,472 --> 00:43:05,105
No matter how I think about it,
I don't get it.

660
00:43:05,838 --> 00:43:08,005
Why was the girl I killed

661
00:43:08,838 --> 00:43:12,138
buried in the ground?

662
00:43:16,038 --> 00:43:17,838
Do you get it?

663
00:43:20,805 --> 00:43:22,205
Should I bury you too?

664
00:43:22,205 --> 00:43:24,505
- Please, spare me.
- Then to your family,

665
00:43:24,505 --> 00:43:26,772
you'll still be alive forever.

666
00:43:26,772 --> 00:43:28,405
How about that?

667
00:44:16,572 --> 00:44:18,805
Did you sleep well?

668
00:44:18,805 --> 00:44:21,372
Sorry, I overslept.

669
00:44:21,372 --> 00:44:26,672
I was worried you wouldn't sleep
in an unfamiliar place, but I'm glad you did.

670
00:44:27,472 --> 00:44:29,072
Sun Young.

671
00:44:32,572 --> 00:44:35,038
Would you like to live here with me?

672
00:44:37,305 --> 00:44:38,738
What about your other family?

673
00:44:38,738 --> 00:44:42,972
Your brothers are all married
and living away, so I'm alone here in Seoul.

674
00:44:43,905 --> 00:44:45,449
Wouldn't you like

675
00:44:45,449 --> 00:44:47,838
to live with me in Seoul?

676
00:44:51,338 --> 00:44:53,238
Would that be okay?

677
00:44:53,238 --> 00:44:56,605
If my existence is revealed to the world...

678
00:44:58,105 --> 00:45:02,172
I plan to reveal the truth
and ask the public for forgiveness.

679
00:45:05,405 --> 00:45:07,273
So you can live proudly

680
00:45:07,273 --> 00:45:09,638
as my daughter.

681
00:45:14,872 --> 00:45:17,605
Thank you for saying that,

682
00:45:17,605 --> 00:45:21,705
- but for me...
- Will you think about it?

683
00:45:21,705 --> 00:45:23,572
Take your time.

684
00:45:23,572 --> 00:45:25,172
No pressure.

685
00:45:35,205 --> 00:45:36,872
As of today,

686
00:45:37,972 --> 00:45:39,972
this is the tenth one.

687
00:45:39,972 --> 00:45:42,672
Jeez, this is driving me crazy.

688
00:45:45,005 --> 00:45:47,072
What on earth is Kang Tae Joo doing?

689
00:45:47,072 --> 00:45:49,238
Didn't he say he found the killer?

690
00:45:50,805 --> 00:45:53,038
Is it another serial murder?

691
00:45:53,038 --> 00:45:54,805
- What should we do?
- Is it the work of the same offender?

692
00:45:54,805 --> 00:45:55,905
The reporters are already...

693
00:45:55,905 --> 00:45:57,872
- Officer Lee!
- Yes, sir.

694
00:45:57,872 --> 00:46:01,805
Pick a few crime scene photos
and send them to the press.

695
00:46:01,805 --> 00:46:03,905
What? The crime scene photos?

696
00:46:03,905 --> 00:46:05,672
Yeah.

697
00:46:05,672 --> 00:46:08,072
What are you doing? Don't make this worse.

698
00:46:08,072 --> 00:46:09,772
It's Prosecutor Cha's order.

699
00:46:21,205 --> 00:46:23,238
Tae Joo,

700
00:46:23,238 --> 00:46:24,905
today's the day.

701
00:46:31,972 --> 00:46:33,972
Hey, why are you so late?
I thought you wouldn't show up.

702
00:46:33,972 --> 00:46:36,672
- Let's go inside quickly.
- Ji Won.

703
00:46:36,672 --> 00:46:38,172
I can't give testimony as a witness today.

704
00:46:38,172 --> 00:46:40,572
What? All of a sudden?

705
00:46:40,572 --> 00:46:41,772
Something urgent came up.

706
00:46:41,772 --> 00:46:44,072
What could be more urgent than this?

707
00:46:44,072 --> 00:46:45,905
This trial decides a person's life.

708
00:46:45,905 --> 00:46:49,505
Even if I testify,
it won't change the outcome.

709
00:46:49,505 --> 00:46:51,472
Are you really going to give up
without even trying?

710
00:46:51,472 --> 00:46:54,038
Did you even watch Im Seok Man's
reenactment video?

711
00:46:54,038 --> 00:46:55,972
Did you even meet Im Seok Man?

712
00:46:55,972 --> 00:46:58,138
I told you! I don't have time for that.

713
00:46:58,138 --> 00:47:00,705
What are you talking about?
Im Seok Man is the suspect you caught.

714
00:47:00,705 --> 00:47:02,905
It's your job to verify
whether he's innocent or not.

715
00:47:02,905 --> 00:47:05,738
If you don't do it, no one else will!

716
00:47:08,505 --> 00:47:10,105
Kang Tae Joo!

717
00:47:12,538 --> 00:47:14,138
Sorry, Ji Won.

718
00:47:14,138 --> 00:47:15,605
I'll explain everything later.

719
00:47:15,605 --> 00:47:17,272
Hey!

720
00:47:17,272 --> 00:47:19,272
Wait, Kang Tae Joo!

721
00:47:25,238 --> 00:47:26,838
Huh?

722
00:47:28,672 --> 00:47:32,038
Where is Detective Kang Tae Joo going?
The trial is about to start.

723
00:47:32,738 --> 00:47:34,438
I'll testify as the witness today.

724
00:47:34,438 --> 00:47:36,338
You?

725
00:47:36,338 --> 00:47:37,972
Yeah.

726
00:47:39,113 --> 00:47:42,705
- He's here.
- He's here.

727
00:47:42,705 --> 00:47:46,038
You called for death penalty for Im Seok Man
in the Kangseng Serial Murder Case.

728
00:47:46,038 --> 00:47:47,657
What are your thoughts on today's trial?

729
00:47:47,657 --> 00:47:51,672
With solid evidence,
I expect a guilty verdict.

730
00:47:51,672 --> 00:47:55,072
Another presumed victim
of the serial killings was found today.

731
00:47:55,072 --> 00:47:56,938
What is your response?

732
00:47:59,338 --> 00:48:02,172
This is already the tenth victim.

733
00:48:02,172 --> 00:48:06,272
In particular, three victims
have appeared in just the past month.

734
00:48:06,272 --> 00:48:09,805
It's truly an unprecedented case.

735
00:48:10,705 --> 00:48:13,572
We will not allow any more victims.

736
00:48:13,572 --> 00:48:19,738
We will catch the serial killer
before another victim appears.

737
00:48:19,738 --> 00:48:21,438
I promise you that.

738
00:48:28,438 --> 00:48:31,472
You testified that you found an error

739
00:48:31,472 --> 00:48:35,705
in the radioactive isotope test
used to identify the defendant.

740
00:48:35,705 --> 00:48:36,805
What exactly was the error?

741
00:48:36,805 --> 00:48:40,272
A radioactive isotope test was conducted
using hair from someone

742
00:48:40,272 --> 00:48:42,972
completely unrelated
to the Kangseng Serial Murder Case,

743
00:48:42,972 --> 00:48:47,072
and it produced a lower error rate
than Im Seok Man's sample.

744
00:48:47,072 --> 00:48:48,438
Your Honor,

745
00:48:48,438 --> 00:48:51,972
we cannot accept results
based on hair of unknown origin.

746
00:48:51,972 --> 00:48:54,972
It belongs to Kim Byeong Cheol, the owner
of the agricultural machinery repair shop

747
00:48:54,972 --> 00:48:56,305
where Im Seok Man worked.

748
00:48:56,305 --> 00:48:58,372
It's mine, sir.

749
00:48:59,505 --> 00:49:01,438
If you doubt it, you can retest

750
00:49:01,438 --> 00:49:04,172
- Mr. Kim Byeong Cheol's hair.
- Kim Byeong Cheol?

751
00:49:04,172 --> 00:49:08,072
Your Honor, I submit
this test report as evidence.

752
00:49:11,872 --> 00:49:13,472
No way.

753
00:49:18,438 --> 00:49:20,738
[Radioisotope Analysis Report]

754
00:49:23,672 --> 00:49:26,905
The radioactive isotope analysis
has been proven to contain errors,

755
00:49:26,905 --> 00:49:31,372
so there is no longer any direct evidence
to identify the defendant

756
00:49:31,372 --> 00:49:34,338
as the perpetrator of the 7th case.

757
00:49:34,338 --> 00:49:38,638
In that case, can we conclude
that the defendant is the killer?

758
00:49:39,405 --> 00:49:42,005
The principle of presumption
of innocence dictates

759
00:49:42,005 --> 00:49:46,405
even if a hundred criminals go free,
we must not wrongfully convict

760
00:49:46,405 --> 00:49:48,338
a single innocent person.

761
00:49:49,238 --> 00:49:52,772
I urge you to uphold that principle.

762
00:49:52,772 --> 00:49:54,372
That is all.

763
00:49:56,305 --> 00:49:59,372
Prosecution, do you have any questions?

764
00:49:59,372 --> 00:50:01,305
Yes, I do.

765
00:50:05,923 --> 00:50:10,138
Then, why didn't the police summon
Mr. Kim Byeong Cheol for questioning?

766
00:50:10,138 --> 00:50:12,205
He seems a far more likely
suspect than Im Seok Man.

767
00:50:12,205 --> 00:50:14,738
Isn't it because Mr. Kim has a solid alibi?

768
00:50:14,738 --> 00:50:15,838
Exactly.

769
00:50:15,838 --> 00:50:17,372
That's precisely the point.

770
00:50:17,372 --> 00:50:21,472
The police didn't arrest Im Seok Man
solely on the radioisotope findings.

771
00:50:21,472 --> 00:50:24,772
They arrested him on suspicion,
and then confirmed a match through testing.

772
00:50:24,772 --> 00:50:26,205
That distinction is very important.

773
00:50:26,205 --> 00:50:28,572
They didn't randomly test people

774
00:50:28,572 --> 00:50:30,538
until they found a match!

775
00:50:30,538 --> 00:50:33,972
I'm saying it was the result
of a rational process of inference.

776
00:50:33,972 --> 00:50:36,905
What if the real killer is
also a factory worker?

777
00:50:36,905 --> 00:50:40,805
What if Im Seok Man just happened to pass by
at the wrong time and got framed?

778
00:50:40,805 --> 00:50:45,372
I remember that day very clearly.

779
00:50:45,372 --> 00:50:48,505
It was the day I was attacked
by the serial killer.

780
00:50:49,638 --> 00:50:52,272
The 7th murder happened
right after I was attacked,

781
00:50:52,272 --> 00:50:54,672
so the police were already deployed.

782
00:50:54,672 --> 00:50:56,772
And Im Seok Man was seen there.

783
00:50:56,772 --> 00:50:59,338
[Defense Counsel, Defendant's Seat]
There was no one else but him.

784
00:50:59,338 --> 00:51:02,305
If there had been someone else,
if the killer had been there,

785
00:51:02,305 --> 00:51:04,772
they would have been seen.

786
00:51:07,672 --> 00:51:09,338
That is all.

787
00:51:10,738 --> 00:51:12,041
[Muwon District Court]
Muwon District Court

788
00:51:12,041 --> 00:51:13,805
1988 Criminal Case No. 142,

789
00:51:13,805 --> 00:51:18,005
I will now deliver the verdict
for defendant Im Seok Man.

790
00:51:18,005 --> 00:51:20,572
While we recognize the flaws

791
00:51:20,572 --> 00:51:23,672
in the radioactive isotope evidence,

792
00:51:23,672 --> 00:51:26,472
we cannot ignore
other circumstantial evidence,

793
00:51:26,472 --> 00:51:29,472
including his presence
at the scene at the time of the crime

794
00:51:29,472 --> 00:51:32,372
and his written confession.

795
00:51:32,372 --> 00:51:35,172
Therefore, we rule as follows.

796
00:51:35,172 --> 00:51:36,438
Verdict,

797
00:51:36,438 --> 00:51:40,772
the defendant, Im Seok Man,
is sentenced to life imprisonment.

798
00:51:46,572 --> 00:51:47,872
What is going on?

799
00:51:47,872 --> 00:51:51,305
Oh dear, that innocent boy...

800
00:52:10,305 --> 00:52:11,938
Seok Man...

801
00:52:24,538 --> 00:52:28,738
[Justice Ministry]

802
00:52:43,238 --> 00:52:46,705
Don't let them say
you're the sister of a murderer.

803
00:52:46,705 --> 00:52:49,405
From now on, just pretend I don't exist.

804
00:52:49,405 --> 00:52:51,572
Ji Hye.

805
00:52:51,572 --> 00:52:53,405
Live happily.

806
00:53:12,872 --> 00:53:18,638
[Radioisotope Analysis Report]

807
00:53:21,072 --> 00:53:23,038
Darn it, you punk!

808
00:53:26,305 --> 00:53:28,305
Kang Tae Joo, darn it!

809
00:53:36,338 --> 00:53:37,338
Kang Tae Joo!

810
00:53:37,338 --> 00:53:40,272
It was definitely Park Sang Beom,
the Modako Club's owner.

811
00:53:40,272 --> 00:53:42,705
Why is Tae Joo
involved with that political thug?

812
00:53:42,705 --> 00:53:44,205
- Ms. Seo.
- Yes?

813
00:53:44,205 --> 00:53:47,072
That woman who came to see you back then.

814
00:53:47,072 --> 00:53:48,172
Which woman?

815
00:53:48,172 --> 00:53:51,438
The one who came with parents
looking for their missing child.

816
00:53:51,438 --> 00:53:55,105
Oh, right! They're putting Hye Jin
on the news today.

817
00:53:55,105 --> 00:53:57,072
- Un Hui, turn on the TV.
- Alright.

818
00:54:02,019 --> 00:54:03,205
Today is...

819
00:54:03,205 --> 00:54:04,338
Mr. Park, where are you going?

820
00:54:04,338 --> 00:54:05,905
[Lee Seok Jin and People]
Hello.

821
00:54:05,905 --> 00:54:08,372
Stop! Switch back to that channel.

822
00:54:08,372 --> 00:54:10,272
This is Lee Seok Jin
of "Lee Seok Jin and People."

823
00:54:10,272 --> 00:54:13,372
[Lee Seok Jin]
Today, I'm joined by Assemblyman Cha Mu Jin.

824
00:54:13,372 --> 00:54:14,972
Welcome.

825
00:54:15,638 --> 00:54:17,872
[Cha Mu Jin]

826
00:54:17,872 --> 00:54:22,438
It must not have been easy to reveal
an illegitimate child as an assemblyman.

827
00:54:22,438 --> 00:54:25,238
What gave you the courage?

828
00:54:25,905 --> 00:54:27,838
When I learned the truth,

829
00:54:27,838 --> 00:54:33,372
I believed the people
need to be informed first.

830
00:54:33,372 --> 00:54:34,738
It was the right thing to do.

831
00:54:34,738 --> 00:54:38,005
Jeez, why is this airing? This was my scoop.

832
00:54:38,005 --> 00:54:39,038
That?

833
00:54:39,038 --> 00:54:40,338
You know, that commission

834
00:54:40,338 --> 00:54:42,972
the publisher's daughter wanted
to give you, Ms. Seo.

835
00:54:42,972 --> 00:54:44,905
Was that about Assemblyman Cha Mu Jin?

836
00:54:44,905 --> 00:54:47,138
No, about his son.

837
00:54:47,138 --> 00:54:50,738
She asked to investigate a woman
suspected of having an affair with his son,

838
00:54:50,738 --> 00:54:52,872
but it turns out they're half-siblings.

839
00:54:52,872 --> 00:54:54,938
Wow, this is just like a weekend soap opera.

840
00:54:54,938 --> 00:54:56,438
That's her.

841
00:54:56,438 --> 00:54:58,805
The woman who came with the couple
looking for their child.

842
00:54:58,805 --> 00:55:00,438
- Who?
- I sincerely apologize.

843
00:55:18,305 --> 00:55:19,905
This is the place?

844
00:55:21,905 --> 00:55:23,738
Let's go.

845
00:55:28,572 --> 00:55:34,038
Yes, we now have a couple desperately
searching for their missing daughter here.

846
00:55:34,038 --> 00:55:36,272
You brought a photo with you.

847
00:55:36,272 --> 00:55:38,538
[Inside the National Police Agency]
Is this girl Hye Jin?

848
00:55:38,538 --> 00:55:40,338
Yes.

849
00:55:40,338 --> 00:55:43,972
She's such a bright, lovely child.

850
00:55:43,972 --> 00:55:46,405
I'm not just saying this
because she's my daughter.

851
00:55:46,405 --> 00:55:51,872
She's the kind of child who makes
you smile just by looking at her.

852
00:55:51,872 --> 00:55:55,205
If anyone has Hye Jin with them,

853
00:55:55,205 --> 00:55:58,505
please, I beg you.

854
00:55:58,505 --> 00:56:01,672
Please send her back home.

855
00:56:01,672 --> 00:56:06,047
If you send her back safely,
we'll never forget your kindness.

856
00:56:06,047 --> 00:56:11,274
- What a poor family.
- Please take a close look at her face here.

857
00:56:20,172 --> 00:56:21,805
Here it is.

858
00:56:23,505 --> 00:56:25,138
You buried the child

859
00:56:25,838 --> 00:56:26,872
in a place like this?

860
00:56:26,872 --> 00:56:30,005
I just did what I was told.

861
00:56:30,005 --> 00:56:33,838
Why are you going this far just to
stay loyal to that punk Cha Si Young?

862
00:56:34,672 --> 00:56:36,938
Are you still afraid of him?

863
00:56:37,705 --> 00:56:39,405
What am I, a kid? Afraid of him?

864
00:56:39,405 --> 00:56:41,672
I've bet my future on Cha Si Young.

865
00:56:41,672 --> 00:56:43,472
- Nonsense!
- Nonsense?

866
00:56:43,472 --> 00:56:44,738
Just wait and see

867
00:56:44,738 --> 00:56:47,305
where Si Young ends up in 20 years.

868
00:56:47,305 --> 00:56:51,005
And what I'll become
standing right next to him.

869
00:56:51,005 --> 00:56:53,105
Oh, right!

870
00:56:53,105 --> 00:56:55,005
You won't be around to see it, huh?

871
00:57:17,405 --> 00:57:19,805
Grab him! Hold him!

872
00:57:28,672 --> 00:57:30,605
You punk!

873
00:57:30,605 --> 00:57:32,205
You!

874
00:57:37,872 --> 00:57:39,805
Tae Joo!

875
00:57:39,805 --> 00:57:43,005
You might actually die today, you know?

876
00:57:43,772 --> 00:57:45,972
Just tell me who the killer is.

877
00:57:45,972 --> 00:57:49,038
Then I'll spare your life.

878
00:57:49,038 --> 00:57:52,705
But that's not what I promised that punk.

879
00:57:53,572 --> 00:57:55,472
Find Hye Jin first.

880
00:57:55,472 --> 00:57:57,272
The killer comes after that.

881
00:57:57,272 --> 00:57:59,638
You little punk!

882
00:57:59,638 --> 00:58:01,772
After everything,
you still don't understand Si Young?

883
00:58:01,772 --> 00:58:04,105
That had nothing to do with Si Young.

884
00:58:04,105 --> 00:58:06,272
Whatever Si Young says goes.

885
00:58:06,272 --> 00:58:09,572
Give Hye Jin back.

886
00:58:10,905 --> 00:58:13,005
You stubborn punk.

887
00:58:13,005 --> 00:58:14,605
Hey.

888
00:58:15,872 --> 00:58:17,672
Say it!

889
00:58:17,672 --> 00:58:20,305
Say it! Who is the killer?

890
00:58:20,305 --> 00:58:21,905
The killer is...

891
00:58:24,438 --> 00:58:27,272
Park Sang Beom, you punk!

892
00:58:27,905 --> 00:58:30,272
You punk!

893
00:58:32,227 --> 00:58:33,865
Darn you!

894
00:58:37,972 --> 00:58:40,372
Get up!

895
00:58:40,372 --> 00:58:42,405
Get up, man!

896
00:58:50,338 --> 00:58:52,172
Coming to your senses now?

897
00:58:54,238 --> 00:58:59,072
Oh dear, your face
is a total mess. What a shame.

898
00:59:01,172 --> 00:59:03,038
You fooled me again.

899
00:59:03,038 --> 00:59:05,538
You're the one who fooled me.

900
00:59:05,538 --> 00:59:10,038
Since the killer's name was never
going to come out of your mouth anyway.

901
00:59:10,038 --> 00:59:12,638
How dare you trick me with this?

902
00:59:15,405 --> 00:59:17,372
I made a public statement today
in front of reporters

903
00:59:17,372 --> 00:59:21,272
and the whole nation,
vowing to catch the real killer.

904
00:59:21,272 --> 00:59:25,172
You made me look like a fraud!

905
00:59:25,172 --> 00:59:27,272
Give Hye Jin back.

906
00:59:29,838 --> 00:59:34,172
Alright, I don't know! I swear!

907
00:59:34,172 --> 00:59:37,538
Why are you doing this, Si Young?

908
00:59:37,538 --> 00:59:39,805
If you just let me find the girl,

909
00:59:40,472 --> 00:59:42,638
I said I'd make it like it never happened.

910
00:59:42,638 --> 00:59:44,905
But why?

911
00:59:48,172 --> 00:59:51,372
How can you just pretend it never happened?

912
00:59:52,105 --> 00:59:54,572
That's not something others do for you.

913
00:59:54,572 --> 00:59:57,038
Unless you make it yourself.

914
01:00:03,405 --> 01:00:05,038
You...

915
01:00:05,905 --> 01:00:09,072
Are you planning to hide Hye Jin forever?

916
01:00:09,072 --> 01:00:10,772
You...

917
01:00:10,772 --> 01:00:14,905
You're taking this to the grave, aren't you?

918
01:00:14,905 --> 01:00:18,772
Jeez, why won't you trust me?

919
01:00:18,772 --> 01:00:20,505
I'm a prosecutor!

920
01:00:20,505 --> 01:00:23,705
What kind of prosecutor buries a child?

921
01:00:23,705 --> 01:00:25,638
Don't you think?

922
01:00:25,638 --> 01:00:28,205
Let's clear up the misunderstanding!

923
01:00:28,205 --> 01:00:30,072
It's a misunderstanding.

924
01:00:39,172 --> 01:00:43,872
I won't even hold it against you
that you tricked me.

925
01:00:43,872 --> 01:00:46,505
Because you misunderstood me too.

926
01:00:46,505 --> 01:00:48,972
We just misunderstood each other, right?

927
01:00:48,972 --> 01:00:51,262
So let's just pretend

928
01:00:51,262 --> 01:00:53,205
today never happened.

929
01:00:53,205 --> 01:00:54,838
Okay?

930
01:00:56,338 --> 01:00:57,805
How?

931
01:00:57,805 --> 01:01:00,905
How can you just pretend it never happened?

932
01:01:00,905 --> 01:01:03,372
You just said it yourself.

933
01:01:05,038 --> 01:01:07,472
I don't accept favors

934
01:01:07,472 --> 01:01:10,338
from people like you, you punk!

935
01:01:11,905 --> 01:01:13,481
I'm going to

936
01:01:13,481 --> 01:01:16,172
reveal all the crimes you committed

937
01:01:16,172 --> 01:01:18,505
against Hye Jin.

938
01:01:18,505 --> 01:01:21,272
I don't care how long it takes.

939
01:01:21,272 --> 01:01:22,665
You!

940
01:01:22,665 --> 01:01:25,905
You can never take that to your grave, never!

941
01:01:27,738 --> 01:01:30,205
You'll regret it

942
01:01:30,205 --> 01:01:32,938
until your dying breath.

943
01:01:32,938 --> 01:01:35,905
Because I'll make sure of it.

944
01:01:35,905 --> 01:01:37,641
No matter what it takes,

945
01:01:37,641 --> 01:01:39,113
I'll make you regret it.

946
01:01:45,605 --> 01:01:47,338
Tae Joo.

947
01:01:50,238 --> 01:01:52,605
If you're going to be like this,

948
01:01:54,838 --> 01:01:56,838
then I have no choice.

949
01:01:59,505 --> 01:02:01,438
I can't help it, either.

950
01:02:11,872 --> 01:02:13,472
Bury him!

951
01:02:17,538 --> 01:02:19,872
Can't believe this is the end for us.

952
01:02:19,872 --> 01:02:21,672
What a shame.

953
01:02:25,105 --> 01:02:27,905
Let's not meet again, Kang Tae Joo.

954
01:02:37,105 --> 01:02:39,805
I'm the one who wants to find that girl.

955
01:02:41,338 --> 01:02:44,005
That girl still hasn't come back.

956
01:02:44,005 --> 01:02:48,572
And her family has been waiting
over 30 years in that house.

957
01:02:54,377 --> 01:02:58,238
It's truly tragic.

958
01:02:58,238 --> 01:03:01,972
I've lost family before,
so I understand that feeling well.

959
01:03:01,972 --> 01:03:05,072
That sense of loss is beyond words.

960
01:03:05,072 --> 01:03:08,838
And yet someone who knows that pain
destroyed another family like that?

961
01:03:11,538 --> 01:03:14,738
Are you trying to blame me right now?

962
01:03:15,972 --> 01:03:18,281
You probably aren't free

963
01:03:18,281 --> 01:03:20,905
from that blame, either.

964
01:03:21,772 --> 01:03:23,805
What do you mean?

965
01:03:25,539 --> 01:03:28,438
[Confession is the beginning of forgiveness,
and forgiveness opens the door to salvation]

966
01:03:28,438 --> 01:03:30,505
This!

967
01:03:30,505 --> 01:03:31,972
[Murder 12+2]

968
01:03:31,972 --> 01:03:34,138
One of these two is a child,

969
01:03:34,138 --> 01:03:37,738
and what do you think the other one is?

970
01:03:40,572 --> 01:03:42,272
Want a hint?

971
01:03:45,205 --> 01:03:46,793
It's another

972
01:03:46,793 --> 01:03:49,372
very unfortunate case.

973
01:03:49,372 --> 01:03:51,337
Because

974
01:03:51,337 --> 01:03:54,072
the wrong person was arrested in my place.

975
01:03:54,772 --> 01:03:56,412
And you

976
01:03:56,412 --> 01:03:59,972
are the one who put him

977
01:04:01,538 --> 01:04:03,138
behind bars.

978
01:04:08,505 --> 01:04:10,138
You mean Im Seok Man?

979
01:04:11,772 --> 01:04:14,372
Don't tell me the 7th case...

980
01:04:15,338 --> 01:04:16,938
Right.

981
01:04:18,505 --> 01:04:20,672
I did that too.

982
01:04:55,905 --> 01:04:58,072
I committed a grave sin against you.

983
01:04:58,072 --> 01:05:00,905
Can you give me my life back?

984
01:05:00,905 --> 01:05:03,205
- I lost my entire youth!
- Seok Man,

985
01:05:03,205 --> 01:05:04,305
let's request a retrial.

986
01:05:04,305 --> 01:05:06,238
This is strong enough to go for it.

987
01:05:06,238 --> 01:05:07,369
[Murder 12+2]
The real killer confessed,

988
01:05:07,369 --> 01:05:08,438
so it's looking pretty good for us.

989
01:05:08,438 --> 01:05:11,272
Why "12+2" instead of 14?

990
01:05:11,272 --> 01:05:12,305
That's unfortunate.

991
01:05:12,305 --> 01:05:13,449
[Searching for the Missing]
That child just

992
01:05:13,449 --> 01:05:15,172
had to pass by there at that very moment.

993
01:05:15,172 --> 01:05:16,205
Yoon Hye Jin?

994
01:05:16,205 --> 01:05:17,805
The child you buried.

995
01:05:17,805 --> 01:05:20,505
Just let him think it was you.

996
01:05:20,505 --> 01:05:23,038
Do you remember Lee Ki Beom?
